what you did last night.

01:51.946 --> 01:53.447
Yeah.

01:53.489 --> 01:56.075
I guess we do have
a lot to talk about.

01:57.827 --> 02:00.663
Master DeSousa,
I'm Miss Aki, your interpreter.

02:00.704 --> 02:02.414
Please this way.
Everything is prepared for you

02:02.456 --> 02:04.166
and your guest.

02:08.419 --> 02:11.507
AKI: Every detail of a Japanese
garden is carefully planned,

02:11.549 --> 02:14.677
from the color of the mosses
to the shape of the pond

02:14.718 --> 02:16.720
to the texture of the rocks.

02:16.762 --> 02:19.306
And seeing the landscape
in miniature helps you reflect

02:19.348 --> 02:22.434
on the transience of life--
to foster an attitude

02:22.476 --> 02:25.312
of appreciation and
a mindfulness of beauty,

02:25.354 --> 02:28.858
which is central
to a well-lived life.

02:28.899 --> 02:30.109
Sorry, I've never
done this before.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.110
Is there anything
I should know

02:31.151 --> 02:33.988
about the tea ceremony?

02:34.029 --> 02:36.073
Boil water, make tea
and drink it.

02:36.115 --> 02:38.075
This is the essence
of the ceremony.

02:40.160 --> 02:43.122
Told you it was pretty wild.

02:43.163 --> 02:45.833
AKI: This is Mrs. Kimura,
our Teishu.

02:45.875 --> 02:47.543
Her family has been doing
the tea ceremony

02:47.585 --> 02:49.086
for many, many generations.

02:49.128 --> 02:50.296
(Aki and Mrs. Kimura
speak Japanese)

02:50.337 --> 02:53.007
RODRIGO/HAILEY:
Konnichiwa.

02:53.048 --> 02:54.425
Here, we wash the hands
and the mouth

02:54.466 --> 02:56.886
to purify our mind and soul.

03:03.392 --> 03:05.019
Please.

03:05.060 --> 03:07.813
Each element of the tea ceremony
is designed to promote

03:07.855 --> 03:11.734
harmony, respect,
purity and tranquility.

03:11.775 --> 03:14.028
You will see that the art of tea
is very simple:

03:14.069 --> 03:16.447
Lay the charcoal so
that it heats the water,

03:16.488 --> 03:18.741
arrange the flowers
as they are in the field,

03:18.782 --> 03:20.784
and give those with whom
you find yourself

03:20.826 --> 03:22.328
every consideration.

03:22.369 --> 03:24.955
Then share a delicious bowl
of tea.

03:24.997 --> 03:26.832
This creates a heart-to-heart
connection,

03:26.874 --> 03:29.209
so that the boundaries
between us come down.

03:29.251 --> 03:32.296
The Buddhists say this is
the main cause of our suffering.

03:35.382 --> 03:37.468
Are we gonna go
through that cat door?

03:37.509 --> 03:39.803
The door is small so that
everyone is at the same level

03:39.845 --> 03:41.597
when they come to take tea.

03:52.024 --> 03:54.860
-But be careful not to touch
the black lines.

03:54.902 --> 03:56.820
Just in case there's a ninja
who might be hiding

03:56.862 --> 03:58.447
under the house,
and who could thrust his sword

03:58.489 --> 04:01.033
up through the mat.

04:01.075 --> 04:02.952
There is always an alcove
in the tea room

04:02.993 --> 04:04.745
with calligraphy
and fresh flowers

04:04.787 --> 04:06.413
reflecting the season.

04:06.455 --> 04:08.374
Please, let's sit.

04:12.336 --> 04:15.130
So, this scroll,
selected by Mrs. Kimura

04:15.172 --> 04:17.800
for this unique occasion,
has the saying:

04:17.841 --> 04:19.551
"Ichi go ichi e."

04:19.593 --> 04:22.513
It means: one life,
one opportunity

04:22.554 --> 04:24.181
to be present with each other

04:24.223 --> 04:26.642
and to pay full attention
to this distinct time

04:26.684 --> 04:28.477
and experience.

04:28.519 --> 04:31.522
Please, take off any jewelry.

04:33.107 --> 04:36.276
This is to not call
undue attention to oneself.

04:44.535 --> 04:46.453
Do you hear the sound
the water makes?

04:46.495 --> 04:50.207
It's called Matsukaze,
or "pine wind."

04:50.249 --> 04:52.418
In the ceremony,
we don't use a thermometer,

04:52.459 --> 04:54.628
but we know when the water
is ready because it makes

04:54.670 --> 04:56.922
the sound of the wind
in the pine trees.

05:11.854 --> 05:14.857
Arigatou gozaimasu.

05:32.166 --> 05:34.168
Ippuku sashi agemasu.

05:36.003 --> 05:38.088
AKI: This is a traditional
greeting that means,

05:38.130 --> 05:40.007
"I'd like to serve you
some tea."

06:20.547 --> 06:24.384
Okashi wo dozo.

06:24.426 --> 06:27.304
Mrs. Kimura has made these
sweets for you, please.

06:27.346 --> 06:29.848
Take the plate
in your left hand...

06:35.854 --> 06:38.857
...and you can cut it with
a wooden pick, if you like.

06:38.899 --> 06:40.984
And then enjoy.

06:49.827 --> 06:53.705
Mm, it's like a little pillow,
you know, from a doll's house.

06:53.747 --> 06:55.582
Very orgasmic.

07:26.822 --> 07:29.283
(wooden implement
clinks lightly)

08:18.999 --> 08:21.793
Arigatou gozaimasu.

08:21.835 --> 08:24.630
AKI:
Since you are the first guest,

08:24.671 --> 08:27.132
