and put it to the side.

08:30.302 --> 08:33.597
And then, you say to your guest,
"Osakini."

08:33.639 --> 08:35.890
"Please excuse me
for going ahead of you."

08:38.434 --> 08:40.812
Osakini.

08:40.854 --> 08:43.065
Excuse me
for going ahead of you.

08:43.106 --> 08:44.358
AKI:
And then, you say,

08:44.399 --> 08:46.735
"Otemae chodai itashimasu,"

08:46.777 --> 08:49.988
or, "Thank you. I'm now
going to drink your tea."

08:50.030 --> 08:53.784
Otemae chodai itashimasu.
Thank you.

08:53.825 --> 08:55.869
I'm gonna drink your tea.

08:55.911 --> 08:58.664
Please place the bowl
in your left hand.

09:00.540 --> 09:03.585
Turn it slightly, as it is
a courtesy to the potter

09:03.627 --> 09:05.337
to not drink
from the best side.

09:05.379 --> 09:09.299
And then, you give thanks
in your heart and take a sip.

09:13.470 --> 09:15.305
And then,
you drink the rest of it.

09:15.347 --> 09:17.766
And the last bit, you can slurp.

09:52.676 --> 09:54.720
Hai Lai!

09:54.761 --> 09:57.848
Wow, this tea
is kind of amazing, right?

09:57.889 --> 10:00.309
Finally we can talk.

10:00.350 --> 10:02.894
I'd rather not
talk about last night.

10:02.936 --> 10:05.147
Yeah, I don't want to
talk about last night, no, no.

10:05.188 --> 10:06.982
I want to talk about
tomorrow night.

10:07.024 --> 10:08.650
I want to talk about
the night after that night.

10:08.692 --> 10:11.153
I want to talk about two weeks,
plus a night.

10:11.194 --> 10:13.572
You know, for everything that's
going on in my life right now,

10:13.613 --> 10:16.700
I have to tell you
it's such contentment I find,

10:16.742 --> 10:18.744
you know,
from being your boyfriend.

10:18.785 --> 10:20.495
Nothing could make me happier.

10:20.537 --> 10:22.205
I need nothing more.

10:22.247 --> 10:25.000
We don't need that crazy
"throw yourself out the window"

10:25.042 --> 10:27.085
-kind of love.
-Right.

10:27.127 --> 10:28.712
'Cause I've already had
that kind of love,

10:28.754 --> 10:30.297
and it's-- I don't know--

10:30.339 --> 10:35.552
I'm-I'm more for a kind of soft
and comfortable,

10:35.594 --> 10:38.263
"I can be your boyfriend"
kind of relationship.

10:38.305 --> 10:40.682
That's just what I want.

10:40.724 --> 10:43.602
Really? Wow.
That-that's really good.

10:43.643 --> 10:44.811
You seem surprised.

10:44.853 --> 10:46.021
Yeah, just a little, yeah.

10:46.063 --> 10:47.689
Why?

10:47.731 --> 10:49.232
I don't know.

10:49.274 --> 10:52.152
I felt that maybe you,
you blamed me

10:52.194 --> 10:56.281
for losing the stupid
competition or something.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.742
What? No, no, no, no, no, no.

10:58.784 --> 11:01.119
You were nothing
but supportive.

11:01.161 --> 11:02.454
Oh, really?

11:02.496 --> 11:03.872
Oh, that's great,
because, you know,

11:03.914 --> 11:05.040
I-I thought you wanted
something from me

11:05.082 --> 11:06.500
that I couldn't give.

11:06.541 --> 11:07.918
That's incredible
that you feel that way.

11:07.959 --> 11:09.294
Who?

11:09.336 --> 11:10.629
You.

11:13.090 --> 11:14.341
Hang on, no.

11:14.383 --> 11:16.968
Hai Lai, don't-don't do this,

11:17.010 --> 11:18.553
because this is
already trippy enough.

11:18.595 --> 11:21.181
I'm not the real Hai Lai.

11:21.223 --> 11:23.642
Real Hai Lai's in the tea room.

11:23.683 --> 11:25.852
I'm the just the Hai Lai
that's in your mind.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.479
So I'll say whatever you want.

11:27.521 --> 11:29.398
This was just a tease?

11:29.439 --> 11:30.607
Be honest with her.

11:30.649 --> 11:32.192
I'm always honest with her.

11:32.234 --> 11:34.277
Just tell her about
your biological necessities,

11:34.319 --> 11:35.737
that-that you cannot
sleep alone.

11:35.779 --> 11:38.031
She knows that
I cannot sleep alone.

11:38.073 --> 11:40.617
We get along, we have a laugh,

11:40.659 --> 11:42.661
we like to be in bed--
you and I--

11:42.702 --> 11:43.829
Hai Lai, a lot, no?

11:43.870 --> 11:45.831
We do.

11:45.872 --> 11:48.959
I just need something more.

11:49.000 --> 11:50.502
What?

11:52.546 --> 11:55.674
Okay, let's just be together,
you and I, you know?

11:55.715 --> 11:57.884
No problems, no dramas.

11:57.926 --> 12:00.637
You like this whole boyfriend
and girlfriend thing, right?

12:00.679 --> 12:02.347
Hai Lai

12:02.389 --> 12:04.433
Oh, man, you blew it.
You blew it.

12:04.474 --> 12:06.643
You cannot tell a girl
that you're not madly,

12:06.685 --> 12:08.437
-deeply in love with her. I...
-It's okay.

12:08.478 --> 12:10.105
With-with real girlfriend
and boyfriend,

12:10.147 --> 12:11.606
you can tell everything.
That's the whole point.

12:11.648 --> 12:13.108
No, no, she said it.

12:13.150 --> 12:14.317
You didn't listen.

12:14.359 --> 12:15.694
She needs something else.

12:15.735 --> 12:17.154
I felt her drifting away.

12:17.195 --> 12:19.197
Yeah, she was drifting away
because that's how you get

12:19.239 --> 12:21.408
to a place that you want to go
in this place.

12:21.450 --> 12:23.952
Well, you-you two have to
evolve with each other.

12:23.994 --> 12:25.162
I don't want to evolve, no.

12:25.203 --> 12:26.872
No, I want to...

12:26.913 --> 12:30.417
I'm enjoying this kind of, oh,
Hamlet-ian crisis right now.

12:30.459 --> 12:32.043
I like it.

12:32.085 --> 12:34.463
I like the comfort
that she gives me.

12:34.504 --> 12:35.630
What's wrong with that?

12:35.672 --> 12:37.424
Comfort?

12:37.466 --> 12:40.760
That's the worst word for
an artist, as far as I can tell.

12:40.802 --> 12:43.638
You know,
you have to grow up, man.

12:43.680 --> 12:45.682
Don't tell me about growing up.

12:45.724 --> 12:48.727
I'm just going through some
work-related crisis right now.

12:48.768 --> 12:50.604
I-- it's so--
you try to confuse me.

12:50.645 --> 12:52.189
Where the fuck are we?

12:52.230 --> 12:54.065
And what kind of a fantasy
is this?

12:54.107 --> 12:55.984
-This is my mind.

12:56.026 --> 12:57.819
Yeah, I'm having some tea
so it's fine.

12:57.861 --> 12:59.779
It's-it's no big deal.

12:59.821 --> 13:01.531
Look, I-I wanted to
tell you something

13:01.573 --> 13:04.284
and I know you probably know
the answer in your heart, but...

13:04.326 --> 13:06.203
-Mm-hmm.
-You know, you've got

13:06.244 --> 13:08.121
a beautiful,
budding relationship

13:08.163 --> 13:10.582
with an extraordinary,
talented young woman.

13:10.624 --> 13:12.918
But you've got to take it
the rest of the way.

13:12.959 --> 13:14.544
Well, I like it the way it is.

13:14.586 --> 13:15.921
"The way it is."

13:15.962 --> 13:17.756
The way it is,
that's a kiss of death.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.466
You have to evolve.

13:19.508 --> 13:23.220
You've got to find
profound new experiences.

13:23.261 --> 13:25.555
I mean, of course,
you've got to have the balls.

13:25.597 --> 13:27.766
I have the balls.

13:27.807 --> 13:30.352
All right, then, as a man,

13:30.393 --> 13:32.145
you have to experience the joy

13:32.187 --> 13:35.982
-of holding your very own child
in your arms. -Mm.

13:36.024 --> 13:38.527
To... to love them,
to smell them,

13:38.568 --> 13:40.445
to live your life through them,

13:40.487 --> 13:43.365
even though they may shit
all over your fingers.

13:43.406 --> 13:45.242
And I want it for you now.

13:45.283 --> 13:48.078
Oh, I was thinking about that,
but... but maybe not now.

13:48.119 --> 13:50.121
Yes, now. This is the time.

13:50.163 --> 13:51.957
Look, you're not
getting any younger.

13:51.998 --> 13:55.377
You know, your-your face,
it's starting to fade a bit,

13:55.418 --> 13:56.878
-No.

13:56.920 --> 13:59.214
I've just got
one question for you.

13:59.256 --> 14:02.175
Is this what she wants, too?

14:05.679 --> 14:07.847
Of course.

14:07.889 --> 14:10.016
Of course,
this is what she wants.

14:17.816 --> 14:20.443
-Oy. -AKI: It's been said
that a bowl of tea

14:20.485 --> 14:24.239
is the universe
held between the palms.

14:24.281 --> 14:27.951
Yeah. Yeah, I-I agree.

14:35.709 --> 14:39.462
Place the bowl in front of you

14:39.504 --> 14:44.259
and then you say,
"Otemae chodai itashimasu."

14:44.301 --> 14:47.095
Otemae chodai itashimasu.

14:47.137 --> 14:49.055
Mm-hmm.

14:50.098 --> 14:52.142
And then...

15:06.031 --> 15:08.658
:
Hello?

15:09.784 --> 15:12.078
Hello!

15:13.872 --> 15:17.042
I'm fucking pissed!

15:18.668 --> 15:22.172
: I wanted
to win that competition!

15:22.213 --> 15:25.175
